The article discusses a letter from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Speaker of the House, in which he reports issuing an Executive Order that expands the national emergency declared in 2014 due to the Russian Federation's recognition of the Donetsk People's Republic and Luhansk People's Republic regions of Ukraine. The order prohibits new investments in these regions, as well as the importation and exportation of goods, services, and technology to and from these regions. It also grants the authority to impose sanctions on individuals and entities operating in these regions or associated with blocked persons. The letter includes a copy of the Executive Order.